  "content": {
    "problemStatement": "There are **N** barmen, given their probabilities **Pi** for passing the interview of a bar. Each barman has a productivity **Bi**. If more than one barman work together their productivity adds up. The bar hires exactly **K** barmen. Find out the expected productivity value of the bar.\n\n\nIf the expected value is of the form **p/q** where **p** and **q** are coprime, print (**p*q-1**) modulo 786433.",
    "constraints": [
      "1&lt;= **N** &lt;=100000",
      "1&lt;= **K** &lt;=N",
      "0&lt;= **Numi** &lt;=100000",
      "1&lt;= **Deni** &lt;=100000",
      "0&lt;= **Bi** &lt;=100000",
      "Sample Input 1:",
      "Sample Output 1:Explanation:Expected value",
      "**= P1 * (1 - P2) * (1 - P3) * (B1) + P2 * (1 - P1) * (1 - P3)(B2) + P3 * (1 - P1) * (1 - P2) * (B3)",
      "=  1/2 * (1 - 1/3) * (1 - 1/3) * (4) + 1/3 * (1 - 1/2) * (1 - 1/3) * (4) + 1/3 * (1 - 1/2) * (1 - 1/3) * (6)",
      "= 2**",
      "Sample Input 2:",
      "Sample Output 2:Explanation:Expected value",
      "**",
      "= P1 * P2 * (1 - P3) * (B1 + B2) + P2 * P3 * (1 - P1)(B2 + B3) + P3 * P1 * (1 - P2) * (B3 + B1)",
      "= 1/2 * 1/3 * (1 - 1/3) * (4 + 4) + 1/3 * 1/3 * (1 - 1/2) * (4 + 6) + 1/3 * 1/2 * (1 - 1/3) * (6 + 4)",
      "= 23/9",
      "**"
    ],
    "inputFormat": "**N****K**\n**N****Numi****Deni****Bi****Pi****Numi/Deni**",
    "outputFormat": "**p/q****p****q****p*q-1**",
    "sampleTestCases": []
  },
